Do not change this setting unless you know what you are doing: most modern distributions of Linux will expect UTF-8 default setting.
During a terminal session (SSH, telnet, rsh, ...), MobaXterm receives a stream of 8-bit bytes from the server, and in order to display them on the terminal it needs to know what character set to interpret them in. Similarly, MobaXterm needs to know how to translate your keystrokes into the encoding the server expects. Unfortunately, there is no satisfactory mechanism for MobaXterm terminal and the server to communicate this information, so it must usually be manually configured.
There are a lot of character sets to choose from. By default MobaXterm will use the UTF-8 encoding, which can represent pretty much any character; data coming from the server is interpreted as UTF-8, and keystrokes are sent UTF-8 encoded. This is what most modern distributions of Linux will expect by default. However, if this is wrong for your server, you can select a different character set using this control.

除非您知道自己在做什么，否则不要更改此设置：大多数现代Linux发行版都希望使用UTF-8默认设置。
在终端会话（SSH，telnet，rsh，…）期间，MobaXterm从服务器接收一个8位字节流，为了在终端上显示它们，它需要知道用什么字符集来解释它们。类似地，MobaXterm需要知道如何将击键转换为服务器期望的编码。不幸的是，对于MobaXterm终端和服务器来说，没有令人满意的机制来传递这些信息，因此通常必须手动配置。
有很多字符集可供选择。默认情况下，MobaXterm将使用UTF-8编码，它可以表示几乎任何字符；来自服务器的数据被解释为UTF-8，并且击键被发送到UTF-8编码。这是大多数现代Linux发行版在默认情况下所期望的。但是，如果这对您的服务器是错误的，您可以使用此控件选择其他字符集。

X11-Forwarding (automatic DISPLAY redirection through SSH channel)

X11-Forwarding is a mechanism that allows the X11 protocol to be routed through an existing SSH channel. The main advantages of this solution are:
- X11 protocol will be encrypted
- X11 protocol can be compressed
- There is no need to set up a new communication channel (and to open communication ports in your firewall) for X11: the network packets go through the already existing SSH connection
